cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it proposes a communication-optimal CNN accelerator architecture. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because it focuses on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are widely used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it deals with optimizing the communication in a system. It may also belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems) because it focuses on designing an efficient accelerator architecture for embedded systems. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it deals with optimizing neural network computations.
